[13,15,16]. It has been shown that by choosing an appropriate U parameter to account for the strong on-site Coulomb repulsion among the localized Ce4 f electrons, it is possible to consistently describe structural, thermodynamic, and electronic properties of CeO2, Ce2O3, and CeO2x, which enables modeling of redox pro- cesses involving ceria-based materials [13,15,16]. The results of our test calculations and previous work [13,15,16] both indicated that only if U = 5 eV and greater can the localization of the Ce4 f elec- trons in the partially reduced ceria be properly described. There- fore, in all the calculations, we fixed the U value at 5 eV.
An energy cutoff of 350 eV was used for the plane wave expan- sion of the PAW. The MonkhorstPack (MP) method [26] was used for the Brillouin Zone sampling. A MP grid of (2 × 2 × 1) was used for all the surface calculations. For the structure optimization, the ionic positions were allowed to relax until the HellmanFeynman forces were less than 0.02 eV/Å. These values have been found to give good convergence for the quantities under consideration here (e.g. the atomic structures, formation energies of oxygen vacancies,etc.).
